  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nTimestamp in message bubbles always displayed on next line after message content. We need to include width of timestamp value and if it fits (along with the text) message bubble max width -> to display it on the same line.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nIf timestamp fits message bubble max width - it  is displayed on the same line with text\r\n<img width=\"355\" alt=\"Screenshot 2019-11-22 at 13 54 48\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/69423971-20511f00-0d30-11ea-9107-9965b2d2b22e.png\">\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nTimestamps in message bubble always occupy the next line\r\n\r\n<img width=\"349\" alt=\"Screenshot 2019-11-22 at 13 54 55\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/69423864-eda72680-0d2f-11ea-8188-dda42593db06.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n\r\n- Open Status and create new account\r\n- Join public chat and send message with 3 chars\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n- Status version: develop 0.14.0 (2019112202)\r\n- Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n",
